Real Gold in Talks With Exchange on Accounts Allegations

-- B y   R e b e c c a   K e e n a n
-- 
2011-06-01T10:17:39Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-01/real-gold-in-talks-with-exchange-on-accounts-allegations-1-.html
Real Gold Mining Ltd. (246)  is gathering
information to respond to queries by the Hong Kong stock
exchange regarding reports in the South China Morning Post that
it may have filed two different sets of accounts.  “The company is confident that it will be able to fully
address the stock exchange’s queries,” the  Inner Mongolia ,
China-based company said in a statement to the exchange today.
Its shares have not traded since last week and it may apply to
resume trading shortly, it said.  “Attempts may have been made to manipulate trading in its
shares,” and the company is considering reporting its concerns
to regulators, Real Gold said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Rebecca Keenan at   rkeenan5@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
